Cart Service
The Cart Service is a microservice that provides functionality for managing user shopping carts in an e-commerce system.

Table of Contents
Features
Technologies
Getting Started
API Documentation
Configuration
Contributing
License
Features
Add items to a user's shopping cart.
Retrieve the contents of a user's shopping cart.
Update the quantity of items in the cart.
Remove items from the cart.
Calculate the total price of the items in the cart.
Integration with payment and order services.
Technologies
The Cart Service is built using the following technologies and frameworks:

Java
Spring Boot
Spring Data JPA
PostgreSQL
Maven
Getting Started
To set up the Cart Service on your local machine, follow these steps:

Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/yourusername/cart-service.git
Navigate to the project directory: cd cart-service
Build the project using Maven: mvn clean install
Start the Cart Service: mvn spring-boot:run
The Cart Service will start on http://localhost:8080.
API Documentation
The Cart Service API is documented using Swagger. You can access the API documentation by visiting http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html in your web browser.

The API endpoints include:

POST /api/cart/items - Add an item to the cart.
GET /api/cart/items - Get all items in the cart.
PUT /api/cart/items/{itemId} - Update the quantity of an item in the cart.
DELETE /api/cart/items/{itemId} - Remove an item from the cart.
GET /api/cart/total - Calculate the total price of items in the cart.
Configuration
The Cart Service can be configured by modifying the application.properties file. The configuration options include database connection details, server port, and other service-specific settings.

Contributing
Contributions are welcome! If you would like to contribute to the Cart Service, please follow these steps:

Fork the repository.
Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix.
Make your changes and commit them.
Push your changes to your forked repository.
Submit a pull request to the main repository.
